Vice President Mike Pence will give the keynote address at the Conference on Prosperity and Security in Central America, on behalf of President Trump. The conference, co-hosted by the US and Mexico, will bring together the Northern Triangle countries of El Salvador, Guatemala, and Honduras to discuss economic, security, and governance agendas. Pence will affirm Trump's support for the countries' commitment to improving security, governance, and economic prosperity, and will hold bilateral meetings with the presidents of El Salvador, Honduras, and Guatemala.